gurmukhi: ਅਛਿੱਦ ਛਿੱਦੇ ਅਦੱਗ ਦਾਗੇ || ਅਚੋਰ ਚੋਰੇ ਅਠੱਗ ਠਾਗੇ ||
transliteration: Achhidd Chide Adagg Daage|| Achor Chore Athagg Thaage||
translation: She has blemished the unblemishabel and has stained the pure one; she as made thieves and thus the persons who are never deceptive;

gurmukhi: ਅਭਿੱਦ ਭਿੱਦੇ ਅਫੋੜ ਫੋੜੇ || ਅਕੱਜ ਕੱਜੇ ਅਜੋੜ ਜੋੜੇ ||੨੨੮||
transliteration: Abhidd Bhidde Aphod Phode|| Akajj Kajje Ajod Jode||228||
translation: She has discriminated the indiscriminate and has broken the unbreakable. She has covered the naked ones and united the disjointed.228.

gurmukhi: ਅਦੱਗ ਦੱਗੇ ਅਮੋੜ ਮੋੜੇ || ਅਖਿੱਚ ਖਿੱਚੇ ਅਜੋੜ ਜੋੜੇ ||
transliteration: Adagg Dagge Amod Mode|| Akhichch Khichche Ajod Jode||
translation: She has burnt the incombustible and can bend the unbendable. She has pulled the pulled the annullable and has untited the disjointed.

gurmukhi: ਅਕੱਢ ਕੱਢੇ ਅਸਾਧ ਸਾਧੇ || ਅਫੱਟ ਫੱਟੇ ਅਫਾਧ ਫਾਧੇ ||੨੨੯||
transliteration: Akaaddd Kaddhe Asaadh Saadhe|| Aphatt Phatte Aphaadh Phaadhe||229||
translation: She has taken out those which can never be taken our and fashioned the unfashionable, she has wounded the unconquerable and has entrapped those who cannot be entrapped.229.

gurmukhi: ਅਧੰਧ ਧੰਧੇ ਅਕੱਜ ਕੱਜੇ || ਅਭਿੰਨ ਭਿੰਨੇ ਅਭੱਜ ਭੱਜੇ ||
transliteration: Adhandh Dhandhe Akajj Kajje|| Abhinn Bhinne Abhajj Bhajje||
translation: She performs all forbidden works and she protects all vicious acts. She creates the sense of friendship in detached ones and the stable one run away when they face her.

gurmukhi: ਅਛੇੜ ਛੇੜੇ ਅਲੱਧ ਲੱਧੇ || ਅਜਿੱਤ ਜਿੱਤੇ ਅਬੱਧ ਬੱਧੇ ||੨੩੦||
transliteration: Achhed Chhede Aladdh Laddhe|| Ajitt Jitte Abaddh Baddhe||230||
translation: She teases the peaceful person and reveals a very mysterious one, she conquers the unconquerable and kills those cannot be killed.230.

gurmukhi: ਅਚੀਰ ਚੀਰ ਅਤੋੜ ਤਾੜੇ || ਅਠੱਟ ਠੱਟੇ ਅਪਾੜ ਪਾੜੇ ||
transliteration: Acheer Chdere Atod Taade|| Athatt Thatte Apaar Paade||
translation: She rips and breaks the hardest one, she establishes the unestablished and tears that which can’t be torn;

gurmukhi: ਅਧੱਕ ਧੱਕੇ ਅਪੰਗ ਪੰਗੇ || ਅਜੁੱਧ ਜੁੱਧੇ ਅਜੰਗ ਜੰਗੇ ||੨੩੧||
transliteration: Adhakk Dhakke Apan Pane|| Ajuddh Juddhe Ajan Jane||231||
translation: She drives the immobile and makes a leper of a healthy person, she engages herself in battle with mighty ones an with whomsoever supremely strong person she fights, she lays obstructions in their art of war and finishes.231.

gurmukhi: ਅਕੁੱਟ ਕੁੱਟੇ ਅਘੁੱਟ ਘਾੲੇ || ਅਚੂਰ ਚੂਰੇ ਅਦਾਵ ਦਾੲੇ ||
transliteration: Akoutt Koutte Aghoutt Ghaae|| Achoor Choore Adaav Daae||
translation: She has defeated the mighty ones and injured the invincible, she crushes those who cannot be crushed, she deceives the undeceivable;

gurmukhi: ਅਭੀਰ ਭੀਰੇ ਅਭੰਗ ਭੰਗੇ || ਅਟੁੱਕ ਟੁੱਕੇ ਅਕੰਗ ਕੰਗੇ ||੨੩੨||
transliteration: Abheer Bhdere Abhan Bhane|| Atoukk Toukke Akan Kane||232||
translation: She frightens the fearless and destroys the indestructible, she break the unbreakable and turns into lepers those of healthy bodies.232.

gurmukhi: ਅਖਿੱਦ ਖੇਦੇ ਅਢਾਹ ਢਾਹੇ || ਅਗੰਜ ਗੰਜੇ ਅਬਾਹ ਬਾਹੇ ||
transliteration: Akhidd Khede Adhaah Dhaahe|| Agadj Gadje Abaah Baahe||
translation: She routs those who take a stand and pulls down those who are firm and stable; she breaks the unbreakable and ride over many, making them her slaves,

gurmukhi: ਅਮੁੰਨ ਮੁੰਨੇ ਅਹੇਹ ਹੇਹੇ || ਵਿਰਚੰਨ ਨਾਰੀ ਤ ਸੁੱਖ ਕੇਹੇ ||੨੩੩||
transliteration: Amounnd Mounnde Aheh Hehe|| Virchannd Naarita Soukkh Kehe||233||
translation: She deceives those who are undeceivable and makes the chaste ones licentious; the house in which the woman has the apprehension, how can there be peace?233.

gurmukhi: ੲਿਹ ਬਿਧਿ ਕੇਕੲੀ ਹਠ ਗਹਯੋ ਬਰ ਮਾਂਗਨ ਨ੍ਰਿਪ ਤੀਰ ||
transliteration: Eh Bidh(i) Kekaihath Gadyo Bar Maanad Nrip Teer||
translation: In this way Kaikeyi persisted in her demand for boons from the king;
